Olivia Harriet (Olive) "Margaret Herron" Dennis formerly Herron

Born 11 Nov 1883 in Emu Bay, Tasmania, Australia

Ancestors

Daughter of John William Herron and Elizabeth (Frimley) Herron

Wife of Clarence Michael James Dennis — married 28 Jun 1917 in Victoria, Australia

[children unknown]

Died 1968 at about age 84 in Frankston, Victoria, Australia

Profile last modified 16 Jul 2022 | Created 17 Oct 2019

This page has been accessed 253 times.

Biography

Olivia 'Olive' Harriet Herron was born on 11th November 1883 at Emu Bay, Tasmania, Australia. She was a daughter of John Herron and Elizabeth Frimley.[1]

Olive married the original Sentimental Bloke, C J Dennis, on 28th June 1917 at Victoria.[2] Clarrie passed away in 1938.

Under the pseudonym, Margaret Herron, Olive wrote My Dear (1928), Seed and Stubble (1936) and the biographical, Down the Years (1953).[3][4]

She passed away, aged 84 years, in 1968 at Frankston, Victoria.[5]
